<HEADLINE>
FT  27 JUL 93 / Commodities and Agriculture: US gold production to rise by 5
per cent
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
US GOLD production will rise by 5 per cent compared with 1992 to 10.3m troy
ounces this year, according to Metals Economics Group, the Canadian
consultancy concern, which based its forecast on company projections. This
follows a 14 per cent or 1.2m ounce jump last year, nearly half of which
came from a doubling of production at American Barrick Resources' Goldstrike
mine in Nevada. Nevada continued to dominate US gold output last year with
48 mines producing 6.5m ounces or two-thirds of the total. California's 14
mines produced just over 1m ounces.
