FT  27 JUL 93 / International Company News: BCE arm warns on provisions
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By ROBERT GIBBENS
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
MONTREAL Trustco, the financial services arm of BCE, recorded a
second-quarter loss of CDollars 22.8m (USDollars 17.5m) after special
charges, against a deficit of CDollars 58.5m a year earlier after special
items, writes Robert Gibbens.
The company warned that further special provisions were likely in the second
half.
MT is one of BCE's last two non-telecommunications assets and may be sold
soon. Talks have been held with at least two Canadian banks.
