FT  27 JUL 93 / UK Company News: Exchange rates assist Shandwick
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By PETER FRANKLIN
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
SHANDWICK, the public relations agency, reported a 12.5 per cent advance in
pre-tax profits - from Pounds 1.54m to Pounds 1.73m - in the six months to
April 30. Turnover grew by Pounds 1.1m to Pounds 80.2m.
The advance in profits arose exclusively from favourable movement in
currency rates, the company said.
Operating profits were up 11.2 per cent, from Pounds 4.35m to Pounds 4.82m,
representing a margin of 9.7 per cent (9.2 per cent).
The accounts have been prepared on an FRS 3 basis and the prior year figures
incorporate costs previously reported as exceptional items.
Interest charges increased to Pounds 3.09m (Pounds 2.81m). Net debt was
Pounds 65.2m, a rise of Pounds 3.1m during the six months. Because of
over-provision for foreign taxes there is no tax charge this time. Earnings
per share came out at 1.7p (0.9p).
