<HEADLINE>
FT  27 JUL 93 / UK Company News: Reorganisation charges reduce CRT to Pounds
3.3m but dividend lifted by 17%
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By CATHERINE MILTON
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
CRT GROUP, the training, recruitment and consultancy company, proposes to
lift the total dividend by 17 per cent despite a fall in pre-tax profits
from Pounds 6.16m to Pounds 3.3m in the year to April 30, hit by one-off
reorganisation costs and the recession.
Mr John Gittins, finance director, said the company used the Pounds 3.2m
(Pounds 3.7m) cash generation as a guide to setting the dividend level,
rather than headline profits.
The pre-tax profits were struck after charges of Pounds 1.5m (Pounds 0.8m)
to cover discontinued and exceptional items.
The exceptional charge has increased from the Pounds 630,000 reported at the
interim stage, reflecting the adoption of the new FRS 3 accounting standard
which meant reclassifying some extraordinary items, together with other
accounting changes and the establishment of provisions against future costs
associated with discontinued activities.
Total turnover, including Pounds 1.28m (Pounds 4.35m) from discontinued
operations, increased to Pounds 47m (Pounds 43.5m) and operating profits
declined to Pounds 4.73m (Pounds 6.07m) including a Pounds 147,000 (Pounds
481,000) loss on discontinued operations.
The company's core training division increased sales to Pounds 22.9m (Pounds
20.2m), contributing operating profits of Pounds 4.5m (Pounds 6.3m).
Mr Karl Chapman, chief executive said: 'The disappointing financial
performance in this division was largely a consequence of substantial
investment in the provision of training materials and improved quality
control processes.'
The company added Wetherby Training Services and Convergent Communications
to the division. The acquisitions contributed Pounds 1.69m to turnover and
Pounds 248,000 to operating profits.
The consultancy division contributed turnover of Pounds 6.5m (Pounds 5.5m)
and operating profits of Pounds 430,000 (Pounds 670,000), following 'a poor
start to the year'.
The recruitment division contributed an improved Pounds 16.4m (Pounds 13.4m)
to sales and operating profit of Pounds 800,000 (Pounds 400,000).
The board proposes a final dividend of 2.15p (1.825p) to give a total for
the year of 2.8p (2.4p). The dividend is payable from earnings per share of
4.2p (8.3p).
</TEXT>
