<HEADLINE>
FT  27 JUL 93 / Losses on deep mines raise sell-off doubts
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By MICHAEL SMITH
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
BRITISH COAL failed to make a profit from its deep-mine operations in the
first quarter of its financial year, raising further doubts about its
attractiveness to private investors in the forthcoming privatisation.
Mr Neil Clarke, corporation chairman, told MPs yesterday that the 30
remaining pits in production made small operating losses in the three months
from the end of March. This compares with what British Coal calls
